body_text:
@asimshankar The reason the memory belongs to ProcessState even after session is closed is because Variables lives longer than session. But with "reset", all variables and other resources are also released.
So for DirectSession, we can release all memory if the "reset" is called. If that is already done that way, we can certainly add that functionality.
What do you think?

